      "message": "[Critical] Line 824: 🔴 Critical Issues - The UI zoom state is reset, but the actual CameraService zoomRatio is not. Because CameraService intentionally preserves zoomRatio across capture-request rebuilds, stopping/restarting local video or destroying the view can leave the camera physically zoomed while currentCameraZoom is back at 1f, making subsequent pinch gestures jump from a stale value. Reset the hardware zoom whenever resetting currentCameraZoom.\n\n```suggestion\nstopCameraProgressiveZoom()\ncurrentCameraZoom \u003d mHardwareService.setCurrentCameraZoom(1f)\n```\nApply the same pattern in onDestroyView() and cameraFlip().",
